<h1>Greater Spirits</h1>
<p>Western Spiritualism - often just called Spiritualism in Seishun - is the belief that spirits inhabit all things found naturally in nature. While some spiritualists worship a specific spirit, most revere nature itself and view it as sacred. While not commonly practiced outside of The CEU, it remains the majority religion on that continent.</p>
<p>Because of how spiritualists practice their faith, it's unusual for them to have a central place of worship. Instead they build shrines to venerate the spirits, which the people of Seishun are known to leave offerings at.</p>

<h2>Nessthiss</h2>
<p>Often called the Lady of Dreams, Nessthiss is a woman known to appear in an oracle’s dreams alongside a massive white snake. She rarely speaks, yet when she does, she always imparts some great truth.</p>
<p>She represents secrets, knowledge, and unanswered questions. She is generally associated with white snakes, which are considered sacred by her followers. While she's said to rarely speak, it's said that she always imparts some great truth when she does.</p>
<p><b>Edicts</b>: Pursuit of knowledge, keeping secrets</p>
<p><b>Anathema</b>: Killing white snakes</p>
<p><b>Primary Region</b>: Seishun, but it's found anywhere</p>

<h1 id="SacredCraftsmen">The Sacred Craftsmen</h1>
<p>The Sacred Craftsmen refers to three gods said to hold dominion over the mountains in Asha and the metals within.</p>
<p>They are legendary craftsmen as much as they are gods, who are said to be responsible for legendary items of unknown make. When a volcano erupts it is said to be the work of Thierna, lighting the forge for one of her creations. When the earth rumbles, it is the work of Adamant transforming iron into the sacred metal that shares his name. When a blacksmith finishes a work unlike any other, he can thank Leabhar, The Mentor, for blessing him in his craft.</p>

<h2>Thierna</h2>
<p>An immortal blacksmith who forges grand creations in Asha's volcanoes, Thierna is said to be responsible for certain powerful items of unknown make. Nothing brings her more joy than seeing what mortals create.</p>
<p><b>Edicts</b>: Passion for a craft, creativity, inspiring others in their work</p>
<p><b>Anathema</b>: Insulting a person's hard work, defacing art</p>
<p><b>Primary Region</b>: Vindral</p>

