<h1>Infernal Deities</h1>
<h2 id="Ekmire">Ekmire</h2>
<p>Ekmire, the Under Prince, is a protector of the weak who lurks in the dark. Some believe him to be a malevolent force who would deliver Asha to the hells, but most would call him a hero willing to fight for anyone in need.</p>
<p><b>Edicts</b>: Protecting the weak, vigilante justice</p>
<p><b>Anathema</b>: Taking away a person's free will, bullying the weak, harming a friendly fiend</p>
<p><b>Primary Region</b>: Vindral</p>

<h2 id="Tarkir">Tarkir</h2>
<p>Often called the Infernal Conqueror, Tarkir believes that mortals need a strong hand to tell them what to do. He’s convinced that he is the strong hand Asha needs and is eager to conquer it.</p>
<p><b>Edicts</b>: Upholding dictatorships</p>
<p><b>Anathema</b>: Freeing criminals</p>
<p><b>Primary Region</b>: Drechen Expanse</p>

<h1>Dead Deities</h1>
<h2 id="kalash">Kalash</h2>
<p>Kalash - more commonly known as the Celestial Emperor - once ruled over all of Akalush as well as the celestial realm. Believing humans to be an immortal species that needed a guiding hand to tell them what to do, he sent celestials to Asha to rule over the mortals he believed too foolish to make the right decisions.</p>
<p><b>Edicts</b>:  Enslaving humans, killing fiends, upholding law</p>
<p><b>Anathema</b>: Killing aasimar</p>
<p><b>Primary Region</b>: Kalshan</p>
